19:07.063 --> 19:17.237
building. It had won two National Architectural 
Awards and was really a building and that was

19:28.979 --> 19:35.185
superior to, equal to, or superior to the other 
elementary schools.

19:39.188 --> 19:45.954
Shortly, as it became necessary, the Kemp High 
School was built. And we simply did not have second

19:45.974 --> 19:56.304
grade schools for the black community here. Brian 
was very fortunate. has been in both the white and

19:57.886 --> 20:25.142
the black area in that

19:57.886 --> 20:25.142
in about 1919 they purchased the electric 
utilities for the specific purpose of financing

19:57.886 --> 20:25.142
the schools

19:57.886 --> 20:25.142
and a lot of people don't know it now but of course 
state financing and federal funding was not

19:57.886 --> 20:25.142
available until 1948 when the Gilmer-Akin bill 
was first passed in Texas. And during the

20:32.867 --> 20:55.028
so-called Depression of 1929 through about 1934, 
virtually

20:32.867 --> 20:55.028
all the school districts, not just in Texas but in 
the United States, could not pay any, they had no

20:32.867 --> 20:55.028
money to pay anybody anyway. They paid in what was 
called script, which was just a promissory note

20:56.138 --> 21:05.531
that someday if they got some money, they'd pay. 
People just had to survive as best they could. But

21:10.358 --> 21:23.496
because of the electric utility funding in Bryan, 
well, there was cash money available. pay

21:24.100 --> 21:34.377
teachers, and as a consequence, the ability to 
recruit the top quality was remarkable.

21:34.817 --> 21:38.243
During that same period of time, the state of Texas 
couldn't pay any salary. The state employees

21:39.425 --> 21:47.458
received script, but not the teachers at A&M 
because they were being paid out of the public

21:48.923 --> 21:54.388
school funds, which came from the public lands of 
Texas, the public school lands. But regular state

21:55.289 --> 22:00.754
offices got paid in script. Those that were 
dependent upon tax revenue, because nobody paid

22:00.774 --> 22:07.340
any taxes in that period of time. Well, supposedly 
they didn't. But in any event,

22:10.543 --> 22:18.711
this built a tremendous stack of teachers and 
particularly in the black schools

22:19.332 --> 22:48.310
and we have just always had real

22:19.332 --> 22:48.310
